grams to examine the cow's fascinating biology, its hard-wired behaviors, and its relationship with humankind.Provides an in-depth look at the evolution of the cow, its role in agriculture, and the development of breedsIncludes chapters on Anatomy & Biology, Society & Behavior, and Cattle & PeopleFeatures a photographic directory of forty global cattle breeds  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCattle breeds. 0aCattlexAnatomy. 0aCattlexProductivity. 0aCowsxBehavior. 0aCowsxHistory. 7aNATURE / Animals / Mammals.2bisacsh  aancestors.  abehavior.  abreeding.  acalves.  acattle.  acoat.  acolors.  acommunication.  acompetition.  adairy.  adigestive system.  adisease.  adomesticated.  aeconomy.  aenvironmental impact.  afarming.  afiber.  aguide.  ahandbook.  ahealth problems.  aherd.  ahierarchy.  ahooves.  ahorns.  ahusbandry.  aillness.  aintelligence.  aintroduction.  alearning.  alife cycle.  amarkings.  ameat.  amemory.  amilk production.  amilk.  apregnancy.  arelated species.  areproductive system.  asenses.  ashow.  askeleton.  ataking care of.  ataxonomy.  ateeth.  awild.  aworking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073912140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691222813zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691222813423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691222813/original  a978-3-11-073912-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles